    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-02-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-02-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="39"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d39">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Dayton</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Seward</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 416.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-02-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 5, 1864.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In conformity with the suggestions in your
                    despatch No. 455, I have called M. Drouyn de l’Huys’s attention to the fact that
                    our government has proposed a convention for the settlement of all claims of
                    French citizens, and that the President in his last message had recommended the
                    establishment of a special tribunal for the settlement of all claims of
                    foreigners which have originated since the commencement of the war, and which it
                    was expected Congress would carry into effect. M. Drouyn de l’Huys said that
                    these matters had not escaped his notice, but he did not see how such tribunals
                    were to get jurisdiction of these questions in respect to foreigners, but he
                    would make a memorandum of the points and consider them further.</p>
                <p>As I know nothing of the details of the proposed measures, I could, of course,
                    give him little information.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WM. L. DAYTON,</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State, &amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
